#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:1
msgid "Variables, Expressions, and Statements"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:3
msgid "Introduce explaining variables (`explain-variables`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:5
msgid ""
"Break down complex expressions by assigning intermediate results to well-"
"named variables. An explaining variable turns an opaque expression into self-"
"documenting code:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:11
msgid "// Good — intent is clear\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:15
msgid "// Bad — reader must parse the whole expression\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:20
msgid ""
"See also: _The Art of Readable Code_, Chapter 8 \"Breaking Down Giant "
"Expressions\"; PR [\\#2083](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/"
"pull/2083#discussion_r2512772091) and [\\#643](https://github.com/asterinas/"
"asterinas/pull/643#discussion_r1497243812)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:25
msgid "Use block expressions to scope temporary state (`block-expressions`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:27
msgid ""
"Use block expressions when temporary variables are only needed to produce "
"one final value. This keeps temporary state local and avoids leaking one-off "
"names into outer scope."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:34
msgid "// Good — intermediate values are scoped to the block\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:40
msgid "// Bad — temporary variables leak into outer scope\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:47
msgid "Use checked or saturating arithmetic (`checked-arithmetic`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:49
msgid ""
"Use checked or saturating arithmetic for operations that could overflow. "
"Prefer explicit overflow handling over silent wrapping:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:55
msgid "// Good — overflow is handled explicitly\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:58
msgid "// Good — clamps instead of wrapping\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:61
msgid "// Bad — may silently wrap in release builds\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/variables-expressions-and-statements.md:66
msgid ""
"If wraparound behavior is intentional, use explicit `wrapping_*` or "
"`overflowing_*` operations and document why wrapping is correct."
msgstr ""
